The course proceeds from the research interests of the students registered every given occasion. PhD students choose the narrower aspect of their thesis that they want to focus on, select the relevant theoretical texts and introduce the texts and their possible applications to other students in the seminars. The course integrates visiting professors when possible.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course provides PhD students with the opportunity to focus on an aspect of their PhD thesis, to read the relevant scholarly literature and to discuss the possible ways of using the aspect in their thesis.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  PhD students who have completed the course 1)	have in-depth knowledge of the chosen sub-topic of their PhD thesis; 2)	can analyse the chosen topic critically from multiple angles; 3)	can interpret the material that they have read and use it for the development of novel approaches; 4)	have the skill of critical reading, participating in an academic discussion and providing constructive feedback.
